title: Google\Cloud\Speech\V2\Config
name: Config
description:
Message representing the config for the Speech-to-Text API. This includes an optional KMS key with which incoming data will be encrypted.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.speech.v2.Config

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The name of the config resource. There is exactly one config resource per project per location. The expected format is projects/{project}/locations/{location}/config.

params.name: data.kms_key_name
params.description: Optional. An optional KMS key name that if present, will be used to encrypt Speech-to-Text resources at-rest. Updating this key will not encrypt existing resources using this key; only new resources will be encrypted using this key. The expected format is projects/{project}/locations/{location}/keyRings/{key_ring}/cryptoKeys/{crypto_key}.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The most recent time this resource was modified.
